<title>UK: Enviromed shareholders seek to change board.</title>
<headline>Enviromed shareholders seek to change board.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-01-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Major shareholders in troubled British healthcare group Enviromed Plc said on Thursday they had called an extraordinary shareholder meeting on January 17 to try to replace Enviromed's board.</p>
<p>U.S. diagnostics company Selfcare Inc, which owns nearly 29 percent of voting shares in the group, launched a fierce attack on the Enviromed board and set out plans to oust managing director Thomas Murphy and chairman Sir Geoffrey Allen.</p>
